  - "water balance"
  - "FAO-56"
  - "irrigation scheduling"
  - "soybean"
  - "MATOPIBA"
  - "PyMC"
abstract: >-
  bwb is a hierarchical Bayesian framework for stochastic water-balance
  modelling and risk-aware irrigation scheduling. It couples the FAO-56
  single-crop-coefficient process equation with a state-space Bayesian
  observation model in PyMC v5, and propagates parametric and meteorological
  uncertainty into probabilistic irrigation recommendations. The framework is
  validated across 10 cities of the MATOPIBA agricultural frontier in Brazil
  (Maranhao, Tocantins, Piaui, Bahia) for 5 soybean cycles (2020-2025).
